Description: Intact pottery small shallow dish with compartments. Wheel-made. Red wash or self slip. Organic red-brown Nile silt fabric.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Great Temenos, Vicinity (outside) of the north-west corner (Hogarth excavations 1903)
Curator's comments: Excavated from the area of the north-west corner of the 'Great Temenos' by Hogarth in 1903. dated by Edgar to the 7th to 5th century BC, but probably 'nearer the earlier limitit', and he cites Saite parallels (Edgar 1905, 125, Fig.5).

Parallels from Naukratis: GR1888,0601.736; 1909,1201.22; from other locations: Defernez, C., La céramique d’époque perse à Tell el- Herr: étude chrono-typologique et comparative, CRIPEL Suppl. 5, vol. 2, Lille, 2003, pl. 2, no. 6 and vol.1, (2001), 52; Aston, D.A., 1990, ‘Stadt und Tempel von Elephantine 17/18 Grabungsbericht: Keramikkomplex 17805A’, MDAIK 46, (1990), 234, no. 17805A, 11, fig. 13.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.024) (Phase 3)
